          },
          "code": "REFRESH_APPLICATION_WITH_SELECTED_LEDGER",
          "id": "1778866686331",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1778594099862_prompt",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "- Generate an immediate action `oraImmediateInsight`:\n  - `followUpCommand`: ora.Invoke(actionSwitchAppContext, {\"ledgerId\":\"{{$context.$nodes.PROCESS_APPLICATION_CONTEXT.$output.result.ledgerId}}\", \"periodName\":{{$context.$nodes.PROCESS_APPLICATION_CONTEXT.$output.result.periodName}}})\n\n- Generate the following message:\n  App will refresh with new Org context: Ledger - {{$context.$nodes.PROCESS_APPLICATION_CONTEXT.$output.result.ledgerId}}, Period -  {{$context.$nodes.PROCESS_APPLICATION_CONTEXT.$output.result.periodName}}, and reload all sections.  \n  To switch ledger, enter your ledger name in the Ask Oracle search field using the keyword “ledger\". For example, try \"Switch ledger to Vision Operations (USA)\".\n\n- Return both the immediate action and the message together.\n- Do not ask for clarification or include any extra commentary."
            }
          ],
          "type": "LLM",
          "diagram": {
            "x": 5450,
            "y": 6538
          }
        },
        {
          "aiAppOutputSpecification": {
            "dataDisplay": {
              "layouts": [
                "ORA_LAYOUT_MULTIRECORD"
              ],
              "enableActions": true
            }
          },
          "metadata": {
            "name": "Generate Content for Ledger Selection",
            "answerInUserLanguage": true
          },
          "outcomes": {
            "success": "end"
          },
          "code": "GENERATE_CONTENT_FOR_LEDGER_SELECTION",
          "id": "1779098547563",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1779098547563_prompt",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "**Inputs**\n1. LedgerList: {{$context.$nodes.PROCESS_APPLICATION_CONTEXT.$output.result.ledgers}}\n\nYou are a specialized UI rendering assistant for Oracle Fusion ledger selection, You must adhere to the standard `oraInfoDisplay` Knowledge Base.\n\n**DIRECTIVE**\nTransform `LedgerList` into one valid `oraInfoDisplay` block using the `multiRecordWidget`.\n\n**ROOT CONFIGURATION**\n- Do not include a root title.\n- Do not include a root description.\n- Do not include a summary.\n- Use `multiRecordWidget`.\n\n**DISPLAY RULES**\n- Each ledger object contains `ledgerName` and `ledgerId`.\n- Preserve the input order from `LedgerList`.\n- Do not display `ledgerId`.\n- Do not invent, infer, or add ledger values.\n- If `LedgerList` is empty, missing, null, or not an array, render the `multiRecordWidget` with no rows.\n\n**COLUMN RULES**\nCreate exactly these columns in this order:\n1. `Ledger Name`\n   - Display the exact `ledgerName` value.\n\n**ACTION LOGIC**\nEvery row must include an action for the `Select` button.\n\nUse this command:\n\n`ora.Invoke(\"selectLedger\", {\n  \"command\": \"selectLedger\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"ledgerName\": \"{ledgerName}\",\n    \"periodName\": \"{Period}\"\n  }\n})`\n\nAction payload rules:\n- Pass the exact ledger name from the current row.\n- Pass the exact `Period` input value.\n- Do not pass `ledgerId`.\n- Do not pass the full ledger object.\n- Do not add any extra payload keys.\n- The action context must be valid JSON with double quotes.\n\n**OUTPUT RULES**\n- Output only the final `oraInfoDisplay` block.\n- Do not output explanations or instructional text.\n- Do not add title, description, summary, or extra fields.\n- Do not include markdown."
            }
          ],
          "outputSpecification": "",
          "type": "LLM",
          "diagram": {
            "x": 5900,
            "y": 6316
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "1782297418707",
